        jTextPane1.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Arial", 0, 18)); // NOI18N
        jTextPane1.setText("1. Agrasen Ki Baoli\nAgrasen Ki Baoli is one of the most refreshing places to visit in Delhi. It became quite popular after Amir Khan's PK movie. In addition to that, believe it or not, it is also infamous for its haunted and scary activities at night. With its 50 m long and 15 m wide stepwell, it attracts tens of thousands of people from around Delhi. You must pay a visit to Agrasen Ki Baoli while exploring the lanes of Connaught Place in Delhi.\n\n2. Akshardham\nLocated on the banks of Yamuna River, this temple was opened to public in the year 2005. It was inaugurated by Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam. Built according to Vastu shastra and Pancharatra Shastra, Akshardham Delhi presents a traditional architecture of Hindu Temples.\nEntry Fee (INR)\n 170 per person for adults (Exhibition)\n 100 per person for children (Exhibition)\n 125 per person for senior citizens (Exhibition)\n 80 per person for adults (Musical Fountain)\n 50 per person for children (Musical Fountain)\n 80 per person for senior citizens (Musical Fountain)\n\n3. Jantar Mantar\nErected in the 16th century by Maharaja Jai Singh of Jaipur, Jantar Mantar is a celestial observatory and one of the exciting sightseer places to visit in Delhi in 2020. Impressive for its resourcefulness, the instruments and tools at Jantar Mantar can no longer be used correctly because of the towering buildings around. The primary devices of the observatory are the Jai Prakash, the Ram Yantra, Samrat Yantra, and the Misra Yantra.\n\n4. The Blue Bar \nIf you wish to explore the nightlife of Delhi, then this is the best pub & grill to head to. It is one of the opulent lounges and bars in the city, and its edgy decor of black on red offers a unique experience to its customers. The hip lighting and the commercial tracks waving in the background will make you hop on the dance floor and dance! And of course, the drinks will just make your day.\n\n5. Okhla Bird Sanctuary\nLocated about 39 Km away from the city centre, Okhla Bird Sanctuary is considered to be one of Delhi's most fun and appealing places; owing to the rustic splendour and tranquillity that this area has to offer. It's resided by the banks of the Yamuna River and is one of the apt places in Delhi for nature lovers and birdwatchers, especially in the Autumn season. The primary devices of the observatory are the Jai Prakash, the Ram Yantra, Samrat Yantra, and the Misra Yantra.\n\n6. Lotus Temple\nLotus structure signifies four religions, namely Hinduism, Islam, Jainism, and Buddhism. This remarkable landmark in Delhi belongs to the Bahai faith, which proclaims that all faiths and religions are integrated. People from all walks of life and religion are welcome here. Boasting an ample space to entertain 2500 visitors; the Lotus temple has nine doors at different entry points. And rightly so, over the years, this landmark has gained several recognition and awards.\n\n7. Select Citywalk \nLocated in the Saket District Centre, Select Citywalk is a premier shopping mall that spreads across a mammoth 1,300,000 square feet. It includes serviced apartments, a multiplex, open plaza, offices, and a food court along with 190 odd retail outlets. It is one of the classiest and finest winter destinations to visit in Delhi and is a paradise for shopaholics.\n\n8. Jama Masjid\nWhen in Delhi, one cannot miss visiting the biggest mosque in India-Jama Masjid. It can hold up to 25000 adherents at a time. Moreover, it was Shah Jahan's first engineering and architectural venture. The mosque has four minarets, and the southern minaret gives a beautiful view of the city. The sheer beauty of this mosque is sure to marvel you. However, ensure you dress suitably to enter the mosque.\n\n9. Nehru Planetarium\nFar-famed as a hub of science and information, Nehru Planetarium also serves as a popular picnic spot for kids. The Nehru Planetarium is sure to bring out the kid in you, and so it is one of the best winter destinations in Delhi! Spend the afternoon wandering about in the vast universe far away from home environed by the planets, stars, and the solar system, or just take a celestial tour to know more about our existence. English and Hindi show last for about 25-30 minutes each.\n\n10. Chandni Chowk\nChandni Chowk is more or less known as the heart of Delhi. This main street of Old Delhi is chaotically competing for space; its narrow roads are packed with shops selling inexpensive yet worthy stuff. And if you are looking for a gastronomic delight, Chandni Chowk is a place to. It has a very famous parathe wali gali where you get every kind of stuffed paratha.");
